WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:04.732
Vera and Clara are built for serious professional work.

2
00:00:04.732 --> 00:00:09.522
That work can require real client data: documents, names and facts.

3
00:00:09.522 --> 00:00:13.025
What you provide is not anonymised automatically.

4
00:00:15.714 --> 00:00:18.958
When useful, local Python tools can filter or

5
00:00:18.958 --> 00:00:22.275
aggregate material before Codex interprets it.

6
00:00:22.275 --> 00:00:27.972
But a mechanical filter cannot decide on its own what the work genuinely needs.

7
00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:33.870
If the task requires them, necessary names,

8
00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:39.768
documents or case facts may be included by Codex in a call to a language model.

9
00:00:42.456 --> 00:00:48.288
That call is governed by your existing ChatGPT plan. In ordinary workflows,

10
00:00:48.288 --> 00:00:51.866
no client or work content is sent to Mparanza.

11
00:00:54.554 --> 00:00:59.731
Optional services hosted by Mparanza have a separate, documented boundary.

12
00:00:59.731 --> 00:01:05.468
For each service, we state what is sent and its access and retention arrangements.

13
00:01:08.156 --> 00:01:12.868
Each workflow is mapped once, when it is added or materially changed.

14
00:01:12.868 --> 00:01:18.468
The relevant boundary appears in the workflow, without paperwork for every prompt.

15
00:01:18.468 --> 00:01:21.200
Professional judgement remains with you.
